    public interface HTMLElement
extends Element
    All HTML element public interfaces derive from this class. Elements that only expose the HTML core attributes are represented by the base HTMLElement public interface. These elements are as follows: special: SUB, SUP, SPAN, BDOfont: TT, I, B, U, S, STRIKE, BIG, SMALL phrase: EM, STRONG, DFN, CODE, SAMP, KBD, VAR, CITE, ACRONYM, ABBRlist: DD, DTNOFRAMES, NOSCRIPTADDRESS, CENTERThe style attribute of an HTML element is accessible through the ElementCSSInlineStyle public interface which is defined in the CSS module [DOM Level 2 Style Sheets and CSS].

    See also the Object Model (DOM) Level 2 HTML Specification

    .
